#MEM id=video-production source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/pixel/skills/custom/video-production/SKILL.md
M|video-production|name: video-prd
M|video-production|description: Pixel's video batch management for Kling and Runway. Covers video QC criteria (motion stability, subject consistency, no flickering), platform format specs, batch sizing, and delivery for
M|video-production|version: 1.0.0
M|video-production|Video generation has different failure modes, different platform specs, and different delivery requirements than image prd. This skill separates video prd from image prd so Pixel can run video batches
M|video-production|| Tool | Best for | YVON use case |
M|video-production||------|----------|---------------|
M|video-production|| Kling 3.0 | High-quality soc video, product motion, lifestyle | Novizio Instagram Reels, TikTok |
M|video-production|| Runway Gen-3 | Fast iteration, creative motion, transitions | Both ventures, short-form testing |
M|video-production|**Prompt format for Kling:** Load `../../../atlas/skills/prompt-systems/kling-3-prompter/SKILL.md` — Atlas writes the prompt, Pixel executes.
M|video-production|| Check | Pass | Fail |
M|video-production||-------|------|------|
M|video-production|| Subject movement | Smooth, continuous, natural | Jitter, stutter, teleporting |
M|video-production|| Camera movement | Consistent direction if specified | Random drift or jump cut |
M|video-production|| Background stability | Static or consistent motion | Background morphing or flickering |
M|video-production|**Common failure cause:** Too many motion descriptors in the prompt (e.g., `slow zoom + pan left + subject walking`). Reduce to one motion instruction.
M|video-production|| Check | Pass | Fail |
M|video-production||-------|------|------|
M|video-production|| Face stability | Same face throughout clip | Face morphing mid-clip |
M|video-production|| Proportion stability | Subject proportions consistent frame to frame | Limbs or body changing size |
M|video-production|| Clothing consistency | Clothing details stay consistent | Pattern or colour shifting |
M|video-production|**Common failure cause:** Long duration clips (>5 seconds) with complex subjects. Shorten the clip or simplify the subject.
M|video-production|| Check | Pass | Fail |
M|video-production||-------|------|------|
M|video-production|| Light source | Single consistent light source throughout | Shadow direction changing mid-clip |
M|video-production|| Colour temperature | Consistent warm/cool throughout | Visible colour shift between frames |
M|video-production|| Exposure | No sudden brightness jumps | Flickering brightness |
M|video-production|**Novizio:**
M|video-production|- No promotional text appearing in video (even for one frame)
M|video-production|- No flat, catalogue-style lighting — must be directional
M|video-production|- Motion must feel editorial, not commercial (avoid fast cuts or hype energy)
M|video-production|**Hourbour:**
M|video-production|- No money imagery appearing in any frame
M|video-production|- Device UI must be legible if shown — blurry or generic UI is a reject
M|video-production|- Tone must be calm and purposeful — avoid urgent or hype motion styles
M|video-production|| Batch size | When to use | ap required |
M|video-production||-----------|------------|------------------|
M|video-production|| 3–5 clips | Style test, new direction validation | Atlas ap |
M|video-production|| 10–15 clips | cg cnt run | Atlas ap |
M|video-production|| 20+ clips | Full cnt library | Stark ap |
M|video-production|**Rule:** Always run a 3-clip test batch before committing to a full video run. Video generation is significantly more expensive than image generation — waste is higher.
M|video-production|| Platform | vtr | Ratio | Resolution | Max duration |
M|video-production||---------|---------|-------|-----------|-------------|
M|video-production|| Instagram Reels | Novizio | 9:16 | 1080×1920 | 90 sec (keep ≤ 30s for best reach) |
M|video-production|| TikTok | Novizio | 9:16 | 1080×1920 | 60 sec (keep ≤ 15s for best reach) |
M|video-production|| Instagram Feed (video) | Novizio | 4:5 or 1:1 | 1080×1350 / 1080×1080 | 60 sec |
M|video-production|| LinkedIn | Hourbour | 16:9 or 1:1 | 1920×1080 / 1080×1080 | 30 sec optimal |
M|video-production|| YouTube Shorts | Hourbour | 9:16 | 1080×1920 | 60 sec |
M|video-production|**File format:** MP4, H.264, AAC audio if applicable.
M|video-production|**Frame rate:** 24fps for editorial/Novizio feel; 30fps for clean/Hourbour feel.
M|video-production|```
M|video-production|Stage 1: BRIEF CONFIRM   — Atlas's video prompt received, platform spec confirmed
M|video-production|Stage 2: TEST BATCH      — gen 3 clips, run full QC criteria
M|video-production|Stage 3: rv          — Pass all 4 criteria? Proceed. Fail? Apply prompt-variation-engine
M|video-production|Stage 4: FULL BATCH      — ap style generates full run
M|video-production|Stage 5: FORMAT          — Export at platform spec (ratio, resolution, frame rate, file format)
M|video-production|Stage 6: DELIVER         — Named files ready for Stark rv
M|video-production|```
M|video-production|**Never skip Stage 2.** A failed full batch wastes 5–10× more generation time than a failed test batch.
M|video-production|File naming for video:
M|video-production|```
M|video-production|[vtr]-[cg]-[platform]-[clip##]-[ratio].[ext]
M|video-production|Examples:
M|video-production|novizio-summer26-reels-clip01-9x16.mp4
M|video-production|hourbour-launch-linkedin-clip01-16x9.mp4
M|video-production|```
M|video-production|Delivery folder structure:
M|video-production|```
M|video-production|[vtr]/[cg]/video/
M|video-production|raw/          ← unedited generation output (keep for 14 days)
M|video-production|qc-pass/      ← passed QC, not yet formatted
M|video-production|formatted/    ← platform-ready, named correctly
M|video-production|rejected/     ← logged rejection reason in filename: clip01-REJECT-flickering.mp4
M|video-production|```